ratings.comment: The entire semester was just a group project where you worked on the same project with the same people all semester. It wasn't that hard. You can't miss more than a few lectures without getting downgraded. She seemed like one of those politically-correct feminist types, which I didn't care for, but oh well.

AWESOME teacher! she is very dedicated and you can tell she really wants to help you get better. if you go in and work with her in her office hours, she is amazing and will help you very much. very nice and respects her students very much. i would recommend her to anyone.

One of those feminist types who talks about equality and crap, you can only miss like 4 lectures per semester, they are totally worthless but the upside is that she is an easy grader, although sometimes unfair, the averages in the class are usually high.
very laid back and interesting. gave few assignments that i actually didn't mind writing

She's a very nice lady.  Doesn't give a whole lot of assignments.  She's a flexible grader.  I really don't like english or writing or anything, but I didn't have a problem with this class.  Laid back style of teaching.  Highly recommended for EPD 155.

Few assignments. Very casual/relaxed class, good discussions. Very nice teacher, understanding, realy wants to help improve writing skills. One big paper on your choice of topic, other small assignments.
Awesome!!  Very helpful and understanding.  Grades fair.
